N:plannotator
D:[plan] Visually review AI coding agent plans and diffs. Annotate in browser UI (delete/insert/replace/comment) → Approve or Send Feedback. Save instantly to Obsidian/Bear from Export→Notes tab without Approving. Supports Code Review (/plannotator-review), image annotation, and auto-save to Obsidian/Bear. Integrates with Claude Code + OpenCode + Gemini CLI + Codex CLI. For manual Plan submission, use python3 JSON (stdin tool_input format) instead of echo/heredoc.
G:plan 계획 planno plannotator plan-review diff-review code-review annotate visual-review claude-code opencode gemini codex image-annotation obsidian export notes bear save scripts 계획검토 설계검토

U[7]:
  scripts/install.sh — Install plannotator CLI (auto-detects OS, --with-plugin option)
  scripts/setup-hook.sh — Automatically adds ExitPlanMode hook to ~/.claude/settings.json
  scripts/check-status.sh — Check overall status of CLI/hooks/env vars/git
  scripts/configure-remote.sh — Configure remote environment variables for SSH/devcontainer/WSL
  scripts/review.sh — Launch code review UI based on git diff (supports commit/branch targeting)
  Plan Review — Open UI via Shift+Tab×2 (Claude) or ExitPlanMode (Gemini) → annotate → Approve/Send Feedback
  Export Notes tab — Click Export button → Notes tab → Save to Obsidian/Bear instantly (no Approve required, hook mode required)
S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Install,bash scripts/install.sh (or --with-plugin to include Claude Code plugin setup instructions)
  2,Hook Setup,bash scripts/setup-hook.sh (or via Claude Code: /plugin install plannotator@plannotator)
  3,Status Check,bash scripts/check-status.sh (validates CLI/hooks/env vars)
  4,Remote Config,bash scripts/configure-remote.sh (or --show to view current config)
  5,Code Review,bash scripts/review.sh (or specify range with HEAD~1/main...HEAD)
  6,Manual Notes Save,Click Export button → Notes tab → Obsidian Save / Bear Save / Save All (green dot shown when configured → changes to Saved)
  7,Manual Plan Submit,Write to /tmp/plan.md then python3 json.dumps(tool_input) | plannotator (avoid echo/heredoc)
R[4]:
  Review plan with planno before coding starts (catch wrong approaches early)
  One concrete action per annotation (avoids ambiguity)
  Always include acceptance criteria in Request Changes
  In remote environments, run configure-remote.sh first, then verify with check-status.sh
E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Install + Hook Setup","bash scripts/install.sh && bash scripts/setup-hook.sh","Installation complete; plan review runs automatically after restarting Claude Code"
  "Plan Review","Agent finishes planning (Shift+Tab×2 or ExitPlanMode) → plannotator UI opens automatically","After annotation: Approve → start implementation / Send Feedback → replanning"
  "Code Review","bash scripts/review.sh (or HEAD~1)","Git diff inline annotation UI → send feedback to agent"
